==================
Token Calculations
==================

Lines: 77 → 38 — 51% fewer lines

Straightforward line count split on \n.


(77 - 38) / 77 = 39 / 77 = 0.506 → 51%
Characters: 1,695 → 1,200 — 29% fewer chars

Counts characters with newlines stripped (newlines are not counted as characters in either format).


(1,695 - 1,200) / 1,695 = 495 / 1,695 = 0.292 → 29%
Est. Tokens: ~565 → ~412 — 27% fewer tokens

This is where it gets interesting. The rule is ~3 characters = 1 token (empirical average for BPE tokenizers used by GPT-4, Claude, Gemini).

But JSON and TOON are treated differently on purpose:

JSON tokens — newlines are stripped before dividing, because in JSON newlines are just visual formatting. The brackets define the structure.

1,695 chars ÷ 3 = 565 tokens
TOON tokens — newlines are kept before dividing, because in TOON newlines are semantic row separators (like CSV). Removing them would misrepresent the actual token cost.

TOON has 38 lines → 37 newline characters
1,200 + 37 = 1,237 chars ÷ 3 = 412 tokens
Token reduction:


(565 - 412) / 565 = 153 / 565 = 0.270 → 27%
